                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200217-127-off738 t18200217-127-crimeloc741"></join>. On the 29th of January the prisoner came into my shop, and looked about, I asked him what he wanted? he said a second-hand bedstead. I asked 14 s.; he left, saying it was too much. In about five minutes, as I was in the back parlour, he crept softly to the end of the shop, took the bed up, and went out with it. I followed and secured him.</p>
